<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880518-0171 </DOCNO><HL> MCI Gets Contract </HL><SO> </SO><CO> MCIC GOVMT </CO><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   MCI Communications Corp. said it received a contract from the Social Security Administration for an 800-service network that will allow the agency to provide 24-hour, toll-free information service to the public.    The one-year contract and two additional one-year renewal options are valued at $60 million and to date mark the telephone concern's largest government contract, MCI said. </TEXT></DOC>